<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Natan, GSS drops just about everytime off emp these days, EER drops off of at least 4/5 mobs. Can't really call those two rare. And i wasnt suggestion &quot;Time&quot; spells should have the same drop rate of those velious end game spells. More like VT mobs or vulak which can drop Ancient spells everytime. - Ghode<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
GSS drops off of one mob with limited access and high participation level necessary to take down.  The Emperor has a limited spawn rate, and even though he is Luclin era, he was not taken down on our server until a few days before the release of PoP (our server is over 3 years old and was a split server).  GSS is most likely the rarest spell in the game.  I doubt any spell compares in rarity, even the ancients as they at least drop in VT.  Perhaps spell research has introduced a few more in the game from rune drops in VT, but I doubt that it has surpassed other spells in availability.  If it is (or was) temporarily more available than an occurrence of a 65 rune spell, with the mass to the elemental planes those will fill spell books at a greater rate.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I don't think anyone else had a similar experience Natan. Just the way it goes though, I have seen it happen for other things. 44 Vulaks pre-SoL and not a single Jaelen's Katana for instance. And those cases are quite similar, as there is nothing you can do with EER and GSS that you couldn't do without them, they are just nice to have if you can get them. - Qaman<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
A Wizard could just use store bought spells against all encounters.  That would not be effective nor efficient, nor would it be balanced if those were your only choices.  Don't get me started on the differences between weapons and spells.  They are more than 'nice to have' but less than class breaking because of availability.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Neet sure, but if you think there was an uproar with Vulak then this will be rather painfull. If they add them (they said they would make melees more powerfull first tho) then expect them to be like Ancients, somewhat usefull smallish upgrades but not that impressive (unless we actually get a cold nuke) Ancient : Strike of Fenin Ro decrease hps by 3000? 6.4 cast time?<br>
<br>
Dont hold your breath, Spell shield +25 is the most you can hope for now : / - F3<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Is an increase in spell damage from 20% focus to 35% focus not enough of a increase for high end players?  Is an increase efficiency from 10% to 30% nothing?  Or perhaps an increase of casting haste from 15% to 23%?  SoE no longer needs to add new spells to make high end players more effective.  If they added new spells they would be affected by the new focus effects compounding the power of the new spells.  There are lots of toys that can be acquired to reward and improve characters without adding new spells to Time; they need to leave some new spells for advancement in the new expansions.  Besides if they do, the next time they increase the level limit it will be used as a base model to give a damage spell to some other class. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
