<br>
Based on the class balance model, warriors are NOT supposed to be damage machines, they are there to take damage and keep the mobs from beating on the casters.  The flaw isn't in their damage output, it's in their lack of taunt ability compared to Paladins and Shadow Knights.  I'm not sure where this, &quot;Melees have fallen behind on their damage output&quot; crap came from.  They have only fallen behind where a screw up &quot;let's make melees not only good tanks, but damage machines too&quot;.  <br>
<br>
The only melee classes that should be able to seriously pump out damage are monks, and rogues.  The other melee classes are fine for their damage output abilities IMO.  Getting upgrades in the high end zones SHOULD be balanced between armor and weapons for the melee classes.  If either of these things arn't balanced, then Verant/Sony can add new items to balance things out.  Then they can go back to Velious and make it so a fair level of caster loot drops THERE for those who arn't in the 61+ range and living in PoP zones.  <br>
<br>
I agree with those who point out that the focus items that drop in Plane of Time and the elemental planes are enough of a compensation between melees and casters.  The idea of better spells in high high end zones/encounters is that those who CAN get loot in those zones deserve to get better equipment and be more powerful as a result.  Focus effects do this for casters just as much as better haste items would, or better ratios on weapons.  <p>Targonis Manastorm<br>
Level 65 Wizard<br>
The Nameless Server<br>
